:"/us/usc/t15/s9501/18","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s9501","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs9501%2F18","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Tribal Government” means the recognized governing body of any Indian or Alaska Native tribe, band, nation, pueblo, village, community, component band, or component reservation, individually identified (including parenthetically) in the list published most recently as of , pursuant to .November 15, 2021section 5131 of title 25","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"19","heading":"Under Secretary","label":"19 Under Secretary","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s9501/19","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t15/s9501","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft15%2Fs9501%2F19","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Under Secretary” means the Under Secretary of Commerce for Minority Business Development, who is appointed as described in section ___3(b) to administer this chapter.1So in original. See References in Text note below.1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
